## Variables

```typescript
// ✅ Specific nouns / noun phrases
const userEmail         = 'user@example.com';
const activeUsers       = [];
const maxRetryAttempts  = 3;
const customerOrderTotal = 100.50;

// ❌ Generic / cryptic
const data  = 'user@example.com';
const arr   = [];
const num   = 3;
const temp  = 100.50;
```

- **Singular** for single items; **plural** for collections
- **Boolean** variables: prefix with `is`, `has`, `can`, `should`, `will`, `did`

```typescript
// ✅
const isAuthenticated  = true;
const hasPermission    = false;
const canEdit          = true;
const shouldRetry      = false;
const isEmpty          = true;

// ❌ — ambiguous, not clearly boolean
const authenticated    = true;
const permission       = false;
const notEmpty         = false; // use positive names
```

