## Functions and Methods

- Use **verb** or **verb phrase**: `get`, `set`, `fetch`, `create`, `delete`, `update`, `calculate`, `validate`, `build`, `parse`, `format`, `handle`, `process`
- Boolean functions: `is`, `has`, `can`

```typescript
// ✅
function getUserById(id: UserId): Promise<User> {}
function calculateTotalPrice(items: CartItem[]): Euros {}
function isValidEmail(email: string): boolean {}
function hasPermission(user: User, action: Action): boolean {}
function createUserAccount(data: CreateUserDto): Promise<User> {}
function deleteExpiredSessions(): Promise<void> {}
function formatCurrency(amount: Euros, locale: string): string {}

// ❌
function process(data: unknown) {}
function doStuff() {}
function check(x: string) {}
function handle() {}
function run() {}
```

