## TypeScript / JavaScript Case Summary

| Construct | Case | Example |
|-----------|------|---------|
| Variables | camelCase | `userName`, `isActive` |
| Functions | camelCase | `getUserById()` |
| Classes | PascalCase | `UserService` |
| Interfaces | PascalCase | `UserRepository` |
| Type aliases | PascalCase | `ApiResponse<T>` |
| Enums | PascalCase (keys: PascalCase or UPPER) | `Permission.Read` |
| Constants | UPPER_SNAKE_CASE | `MAX_RETRIES` |
| Files (non-component) | kebab-case | `user-service.ts` |
| Files (components) | PascalCase | `UserProfile.tsx` |

### Private Members — Modern TS
```typescript
class UserService {
  // ✅ TypeScript private keyword — compile-time enforcement
  private readonly apiClient: ApiClient;

  // ✅ ECMAScript # private fields — true runtime privacy
  #cache = new Map<string, User>();

  // ❌ Underscore prefix — legacy convention, offers no actual privacy
  _privateMethod() {} // avoid in new code
}
```

