## REST API Endpoints

```
# ✅ Nouns, plural, kebab-case, versioned
GET    /v1/users
GET    /v1/users/:userId
POST   /v1/users
PATCH  /v1/users/:userId
DELETE /v1/users/:userId
GET    /v1/users/:userId/orders
GET    /v1/users?status=active&limit=20&cursor=xxx

# ❌
GET  /getUsers
GET  /user
POST /createUser
GET  /userOrders/:id
```

- Use `PATCH` for partial updates, `PUT` for full replacement
- Use `cursor`-based pagination over `offset` for large datasets
- Query params for filtering/sorting/pagination — path params for resource identity

