## Anti-Patterns to Avoid

| Anti-pattern | Example | Fix |
|-------------|---------|-----|
| Single letters | `x`, `y`, `n` | Only `i`, `j`, `k` in loops |
| Abbreviations | `usr`, `mgr`, `cfg` | `user`, `manager`, `config` |
| Generic nouns | `data`, `info`, `value` | `userData`, `configValue` |
| Hungarian notation | `strName`, `intCount` | `name`, `count` |
| Differs only by case | `user` + `User` in same scope | rename one |
| Negative booleans | `isNotEmpty`, `hasNoPermission` | `isEmpty`, `hasPermission` |
| Misleading names | `getUser()` that also mutates | `fetchAndCacheUser()` |

---

## Review Checklist

- [ ] Names reveal intent — no abbreviations, no generics
- [ ] Boolean variables/functions use `is`, `has`, `can` prefix
- [ ] Functions use action verbs
- [ ] Classes/types/interfaces are nouns (PascalCase)
- [ ] Constants are UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
- [ ] Files match their primary export
- [ ] DB tables/columns follow snake_case convention
- [ ] REST endpoints are nouns, plural, versioned
- [ ] No underscore-prefixed private members in new TypeScript code
